45constexpr const char* kPixelLimitResourceFieldTrialName =
46 "WebRTC-PixelLimitResource";

48bool IsResolutionScalingEnabled(DegradationPreference degradation_preference) {
49 return degradation_preference == DegradationPreference::MAINTAIN_FRAMERATE ||
50 degradation_preference == DegradationPreference::BALANCED;
51}
52
53bool IsFramerateScalingEnabled(DegradationPreference degradation_preference) {
54 return degradation_preference == DegradationPreference::MAINTAIN_RESOLUTION ||
55 degradation_preference == DegradationPreference::BALANCED;
56}
57
58std::string ToString(VideoAdaptationReason reason) {
59 switch (reason) {
60 case VideoAdaptationReason::kQuality:
61 return "quality";
62 case VideoAdaptationReason::kCpu:
63 return "cpu";
64 }
65 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
66}
67
68std::vector<bool> GetActiveLayersFlags(const VideoCodec& codec) {
69 std::vector<bool> flags;
70 if (codec.codecType == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP9) {
71 flags.resize(codec.VP9().numberOfSpatialLayers);
72 for (size_t i = 0; i < flags.size(); ++i) {
73 flags[i] = codec.spatialLayers[i].active;
74 }
75 } else {
76 flags.resize(codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams);
77 for (size_t i = 0; i < flags.size(); ++i) {
78 flags[i] = codec.simulcastStream[i].active;
79 }
80 }
81 return flags;
82}
83
84bool EqualFlags(const std::vector<bool>& a, const std::vector<bool>& b) {
85 if (a.size() != b.size())
86 return false;
87 return std::equal(a.begin(), a.end(), b.begin());
88}

92class VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::InitialFrameDropper {
93 public:
94 explicit InitialFrameDropper(
95 rtc::scoped_refptr<QualityScalerResource> quality_scaler_resource)
96 : quality_scaler_resource_(quality_scaler_resource),
97 quality_scaler_settings_(QualityScalerSettings::ParseFromFieldTrials()),
98 has_seen_first_bwe_drop_(false),
99 set_start_bitrate_(DataRate::Zero()),
100 set_start_bitrate_time_ms_(0),
101 initial_framedrop_(0),
102 use_bandwidth_allocation_(false),
103 bandwidth_allocation_(DataRate::Zero()),
104 last_input_width_(0),
105 last_input_height_(0) {
106 RTC_DCHECK(quality_scaler_resource_);
107 }
108
109 // Output signal.
110 bool DropInitialFrames() const {
111 return initial_framedrop_ < kMaxInitialFramedrop;
112 }
113
114 absl::optional<uint32_t> single_active_stream_pixels() const {
115 return single_active_stream_pixels_;
116 }
117
118 absl::optional<uint32_t> UseBandwidthAllocationBps() const {
119 return (use_bandwidth_allocation_ &&
120 bandwidth_allocation_ > DataRate::Zero())
121 ? absl::optional<uint32_t>(bandwidth_allocation_.bps())
122 : absl::nullopt;
123 }
124
125 // Input signals.
126 void SetStartBitrate(DataRate start_bitrate, int64_t now_ms) {
127 set_start_bitrate_ = start_bitrate;
128 set_start_bitrate_time_ms_ = now_ms;
129 }
130
131 void SetBandwidthAllocation(DataRate bandwidth_allocation) {
132 bandwidth_allocation_ = bandwidth_allocation;
133 }
134
135 void SetTargetBitrate(DataRate target_bitrate, int64_t now_ms) {
136 if (set_start_bitrate_ > DataRate::Zero() && !has_seen_first_bwe_drop_ &&
137 quality_scaler_resource_->is_started() &&
138 quality_scaler_settings_.InitialBitrateIntervalMs() &&
139 quality_scaler_settings_.InitialBitrateFactor()) {
140 int64_t diff_ms = now_ms - set_start_bitrate_time_ms_;
141 if (diff_ms <
142 quality_scaler_settings_.InitialBitrateIntervalMs().value() &&
143 (target_bitrate <
144 (set_start_bitrate_ *
145 quality_scaler_settings_.InitialBitrateFactor().value()))) {
146 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Reset initial_framedrop_. Start bitrate: "
147 << set_start_bitrate_.bps()
148 << ", target bitrate: " << target_bitrate.bps();
149 initial_framedrop_ = 0;
150 has_seen_first_bwe_drop_ = true;
151 }
152 }
153 }
154
155 void OnEncoderSettingsUpdated(
156 const VideoCodec& codec,
157 const VideoAdaptationCounters& adaptation_counters) {
158 std::vector<bool> active_flags = GetActiveLayersFlags(codec);
159 // Check if the source resolution has changed for the external reasons,
160 // i.e. without any adaptation from WebRTC.
161 const bool source_resolution_changed =
162 (last_input_width_ != codec.width ||
163 last_input_height_ != codec.height) &&
164 adaptation_counters.resolution_adaptations ==
165 last_adaptation_counters_.resolution_adaptations;
166 if (!EqualFlags(active_flags, last_active_flags_) ||
167 source_resolution_changed) {
168 // Streams configuration has changed.
169 // Initial frame drop must be enabled because BWE might be way too low
170 // for the selected resolution.
171 if (quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
172 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Resetting initial_framedrop_ due to changed "
173 "stream parameters";
174 initial_framedrop_ = 0;
175 if (single_active_stream_pixels_ &&
176 VideoStreamAdapter::GetSingleActiveLayerPixels(codec) >
177 *single_active_stream_pixels_) {
178 // Resolution increased.
179 use_bandwidth_allocation_ = true;
180 }
181 }
182 }
183 last_adaptation_counters_ = adaptation_counters;
184 last_active_flags_ = active_flags;
185 last_input_width_ = codec.width;
186 last_input_height_ = codec.height;
187 single_active_stream_pixels_ =
188 VideoStreamAdapter::GetSingleActiveLayerPixels(codec);
189 }
190
191 void OnFrameDroppedDueToSize() { ++initial_framedrop_; }
192
193 void Disable() {
194 initial_framedrop_ = kMaxInitialFramedrop;
195 use_bandwidth_allocation_ = false;
196 }
197
198 void OnQualityScalerSettingsUpdated() {
199 if (quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
200 // Restart frame drops due to size.
201 initial_framedrop_ = 0;
202 } else {
203 // Quality scaling disabled so we shouldn't drop initial frames.
204 Disable();
205 }
206 }
207
208 private:
209 // The maximum number of frames to drop at beginning of stream to try and
210 // achieve desired bitrate.
211 static const int kMaxInitialFramedrop = 4;
212
213 const rtc::scoped_refptr<QualityScalerResource> quality_scaler_resource_;
214 const QualityScalerSettings quality_scaler_settings_;
215 bool has_seen_first_bwe_drop_;
216 DataRate set_start_bitrate_;
217 int64_t set_start_bitrate_time_ms_;
218 // Counts how many frames we've dropped in the initial framedrop phase.
219 int initial_framedrop_;
220 absl::optional<uint32_t> single_active_stream_pixels_;
221 bool use_bandwidth_allocation_;
222 DataRate bandwidth_allocation_;
223
224 std::vector<bool> last_active_flags_;
225 VideoAdaptationCounters last_adaptation_counters_;
226 int last_input_width_;
227 int last_input_height_;
228};

230VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager(
231 VideoStreamInputStateProvider* input_state_provider,
232 VideoStreamEncoderObserver* encoder_stats_observer,
233 Clock* clock,
234 bool experiment_cpu_load_estimator,
235 std::unique_ptr<OveruseFrameDetector> overuse_detector,
236 DegradationPreferenceProvider* degradation_preference_provider)
237 : degradation_preference_provider_(degradation_preference_provider),
238 bitrate_constraint_(std::make_unique<BitrateConstraint>()),
239 balanced_constraint_(std::make_unique<BalancedConstraint>(
240 degradation_preference_provider_)),
241 encode_usage_resource_(
242 EncodeUsageResource::Create(std::move(overuse_detector))),
243 quality_scaler_resource_(QualityScalerResource::Create()),
244 pixel_limit_resource_(nullptr),
245 encoder_queue_(nullptr),
246 input_state_provider_(input_state_provider),
247 adaptation_processor_(nullptr),
248 encoder_stats_observer_(encoder_stats_observer),
249 degradation_preference_(DegradationPreference::DISABLED),
250 video_source_restrictions_(),
251 clock_(clock),
252 experiment_cpu_load_estimator_(experiment_cpu_load_estimator),
253 initial_frame_dropper_(
254 std::make_unique<InitialFrameDropper>(quality_scaler_resource_)),
255 quality_scaling_experiment_enabled_(QualityScalingExperiment::Enabled()),
256 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_(absl::nullopt),
257 quality_rampup_experiment_(
258 QualityRampUpExperimentHelper::CreateIfEnabled(this, clock_)),
259 encoder_settings_(absl::nullopt) {
260 RTC_CHECK(degradation_preference_provider_);
261 RTC_CHECK(encoder_stats_observer_);
262}

297void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::ConfigureEncodeUsageResource() {
298 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
299 RTC_DCHECK(encoder_settings_.has_value());
300 if (encode_usage_resource_->is_started()) {
301 encode_usage_resource_->StopCheckForOveruse();
302 } else {
303 // If the resource has not yet started then it needs to be added.
304 AddResource(encode_usage_resource_, VideoAdaptationReason::kCpu);
305 }
306 encode_usage_resource_->StartCheckForOveruse(GetCpuOveruseOptions());
307}
308
309void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::MaybeInitializePixelLimitResource() {
310 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
311 RTC_DCHECK(adaptation_processor_);
312 RTC_DCHECK(!pixel_limit_resource_);
313 if (!field_trial::IsEnabled(kPixelLimitResourceFieldTrialName)) {
314 // The field trial is not running.
315 return;
316 }
317 int max_pixels = 0;
318 std::string pixel_limit_field_trial =
319 field_trial::FindFullName(kPixelLimitResourceFieldTrialName);
320 if (sscanf(pixel_limit_field_trial.c_str(), "Enabled-%d", &max_pixels) != 1) {
321 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Couldn't parse " << kPixelLimitResourceFieldTrialName
322 << " trial config: " << pixel_limit_field_trial;
323 return;
324 }
325 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Running field trial "
326 << kPixelLimitResourceFieldTrialName << " configured to "
327 << max_pixels << " max pixels";
328 // Configure the specified max pixels from the field trial. The pixel limit
329 // resource is active for the lifetme of the stream (until
330 // StopManagedResources() is called).
331 pixel_limit_resource_ =
332 PixelLimitResource::Create(encoder_queue_->Get(), input_state_provider_);
333 pixel_limit_resource_->SetMaxPixels(max_pixels);
334 AddResource(pixel_limit_resource_, VideoAdaptationReason::kCpu);
335}
336
337void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::StopManagedResources() {
338 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
339 RTC_DCHECK(adaptation_processor_);
340 if (encode_usage_resource_->is_started()) {
341 encode_usage_resource_->StopCheckForOveruse();
342 RemoveResource(encode_usage_resource_);
343 }
344 if (quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
345 quality_scaler_resource_->StopCheckForOveruse();
346 RemoveResource(quality_scaler_resource_);
347 }
348 if (pixel_limit_resource_) {
349 RemoveResource(pixel_limit_resource_);
350 pixel_limit_resource_ = nullptr;
351 }
352}
353
354void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::AddResource(
355 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource,
356 VideoAdaptationReason reason) {
357 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
358 RTC_DCHECK(resource);
359 bool inserted;
360 std::tie(std::ignore, inserted) = resources_.emplace(resource, reason);
361 RTC_DCHECK(inserted) << "Resource " << resource->Name()
362 << " already was inserted";
363 adaptation_processor_->AddResource(resource);
364}
365
366void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::RemoveResource(
367 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource) {
368 {
369 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
370 RTC_DCHECK(resource);
371 const auto& it = resources_.find(resource);
372 RTC_DCHECK(it != resources_.end())
373 << "Resource \"" << resource->Name() << "\" not found.";
374 resources_.erase(it);
375 }
376 adaptation_processor_->RemoveResource(resource);
377}

385void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::SetEncoderSettings(
386 EncoderSettings encoder_settings) {
387 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
388 encoder_settings_ = std::move(encoder_settings);
389 bitrate_constraint_->OnEncoderSettingsUpdated(encoder_settings_);
390 initial_frame_dropper_->OnEncoderSettingsUpdated(
391 encoder_settings_->video_codec(), current_adaptation_counters_);
392 MaybeUpdateTargetFrameRate();
393}

395void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::SetStartBitrate(
396 DataRate start_bitrate) {
397 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
398 if (!start_bitrate.IsZero()) {
399 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_ = start_bitrate.bps();
400 bitrate_constraint_->OnEncoderTargetBitrateUpdated(
401 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_);
402 balanced_constraint_->OnEncoderTargetBitrateUpdated(
403 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_);
404 }
405 initial_frame_dropper_->SetStartBitrate(start_bitrate,
406 clock_->TimeInMicroseconds());
407}

409void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::SetTargetBitrate(
410 DataRate target_bitrate) {
411 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
412 if (!target_bitrate.IsZero()) {
413 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_ = target_bitrate.bps();
414 bitrate_constraint_->OnEncoderTargetBitrateUpdated(
415 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_);
416 balanced_constraint_->OnEncoderTargetBitrateUpdated(
417 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_);
418 }
419 initial_frame_dropper_->SetTargetBitrate(target_bitrate,
420 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
421}

431void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::OnFrameDroppedDueToSize() {
432 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
433 initial_frame_dropper_->OnFrameDroppedDueToSize();
434 Adaptation reduce_resolution = stream_adapter_->GetAdaptDownResolution();
435 if (reduce_resolution.status() == Adaptation::Status::kValid) {
436 stream_adapter_->ApplyAdaptation(reduce_resolution,
437 quality_scaler_resource_);
438 }
439}

449void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::OnEncodeCompleted(
450 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
451 int64_t time_sent_in_us,
452 absl::optional<int> encode_duration_us) {
453 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
454 // Inform |encode_usage_resource_| of the encode completed event.
455 uint32_t timestamp = encoded_image.Timestamp();
456 int64_t capture_time_us =
457 encoded_image.capture_time_ms_ * rtc::kNumMicrosecsPerMillisec;
458 encode_usage_resource_->OnEncodeCompleted(
459 timestamp, time_sent_in_us, capture_time_us, encode_duration_us);
460 quality_scaler_resource_->OnEncodeCompleted(encoded_image, time_sent_in_us);
461}

485
486void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::OnMaybeEncodeFrame() {
487 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
488 initial_frame_dropper_->Disable();
489 if (quality_rampup_experiment_ && quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
490 DataRate bandwidth = encoder_rates_.has_value()
491 ? encoder_rates_->bandwidth_allocation
492 : DataRate::Zero();
493 quality_rampup_experiment_->PerformQualityRampupExperiment(
494 quality_scaler_resource_, bandwidth,
495 DataRate::BitsPerSec(encoder_target_bitrate_bps_.value_or(0)),
496 DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(encoder_settings_->video_codec().maxBitrate),
497 LastInputFrameSizeOrDefault());
498 }
499}
500
501void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::UpdateQualityScalerSettings(
502 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::QpThresholds> qp_thresholds) {
503 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
504 if (qp_thresholds.has_value()) {
505 if (quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
506 quality_scaler_resource_->SetQpThresholds(qp_thresholds.value());
507 } else {
508 quality_scaler_resource_->StartCheckForOveruse(qp_thresholds.value());
509 AddResource(quality_scaler_resource_, VideoAdaptationReason::kQuality);
510 }
511 } else if (quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
512 quality_scaler_resource_->StopCheckForOveruse();
513 RemoveResource(quality_scaler_resource_);
514 }
515 initial_frame_dropper_->OnQualityScalerSettingsUpdated();
516}
517
518void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::ConfigureQualityScaler(
519 const VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo& encoder_info) {
520 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
521 const auto scaling_settings = encoder_info.scaling_settings;
522 const bool quality_scaling_allowed =
523 IsResolutionScalingEnabled(degradation_preference_) &&
524 (scaling_settings.thresholds.has_value() ||
525 (encoder_settings_.has_value() &&
526 encoder_settings_->encoder_config().is_quality_scaling_allowed));
527
528 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/11222): Should this move to
529 // QualityScalerResource?
530 if (quality_scaling_allowed) {
531 if (!quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
532 // Quality scaler has not already been configured.
533
534 // Use experimental thresholds if available.
535 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::QpThresholds> experimental_thresholds;
536 if (quality_scaling_experiment_enabled_) {
537 experimental_thresholds = QualityScalingExperiment::GetQpThresholds(
538 GetVideoCodecTypeOrGeneric(encoder_settings_));
539 }
540 UpdateQualityScalerSettings(experimental_thresholds.has_value()
541 ? experimental_thresholds
542 : scaling_settings.thresholds);
543 }
544 } else {
545 UpdateQualityScalerSettings(absl::nullopt);
546 }
547
548 // Set the qp-thresholds to the balanced settings if balanced mode.
549 if (degradation_preference_ == DegradationPreference::BALANCED &&
550 quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()) {
551 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::QpThresholds> thresholds =
552 balanced_settings_.GetQpThresholds(
553 GetVideoCodecTypeOrGeneric(encoder_settings_),
554 LastInputFrameSizeOrDefault());
555 if (thresholds) {
556 quality_scaler_resource_->SetQpThresholds(*thresholds);
557 }
558 }
559 UpdateStatsAdaptationSettings();
560}
561
562VideoAdaptationReason VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::GetReasonFromResource(
563 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource) const {
564 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
565 const auto& registered_resource = resources_.find(resource);
566 RTC_DCHECK(registered_resource != resources_.end())
567 << resource->Name() << " not found.";
568 return registered_resource->second;
569}
570
571// TODO(pbos): Lower these thresholds (to closer to 100%) when we handle
572// pipelining encoders better (multiple input frames before something comes
573// out). This should effectively turn off CPU adaptations for systems that
574// remotely cope with the load right now.
575CpuOveruseOptions VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::GetCpuOveruseOptions()
576 const {
577 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
578 // This is already ensured by the only caller of this method:
579 // StartResourceAdaptation().
580 RTC_DCHECK(encoder_settings_.has_value());
581 CpuOveruseOptions options;
582 // Hardware accelerated encoders are assumed to be pipelined; give them
583 // additional overuse time.
584 if (encoder_settings_->encoder_info().is_hardware_accelerated) {
585 options.low_encode_usage_threshold_percent = 150;
586 options.high_encode_usage_threshold_percent = 200;
587 }
588 if (experiment_cpu_load_estimator_) {
589 options.filter_time_ms = 5 * rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
590 }
591 return options;
592}
593
594int VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::LastInputFrameSizeOrDefault() const {
595 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
596 return input_state_provider_->InputState().frame_size_pixels().value_or(
597 kDefaultInputPixelsWidth * kDefaultInputPixelsHeight);
598}
599
600void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::OnVideoSourceRestrictionsUpdated(
601 VideoSourceRestrictions restrictions,
602 const VideoAdaptationCounters& adaptation_counters,
603 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> reason,
604 const VideoSourceRestrictions& unfiltered_restrictions) {
605 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
606 current_adaptation_counters_ = adaptation_counters;
607
608 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11553) Remove reason parameter and add reset callback.
609 if (!reason && adaptation_counters.Total() == 0) {
610 // Adaptation was manually reset - clear the per-reason counters too.
611 encoder_stats_observer_->ClearAdaptationStats();
612 }
613
614 video_source_restrictions_ = FilterRestrictionsByDegradationPreference(
615 restrictions, degradation_preference_);
616 MaybeUpdateTargetFrameRate();
617}
618
619void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::OnResourceLimitationChanged(
620 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource,
621 const std::map<rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource>, VideoAdaptationCounters>&
622 resource_limitations) {
623 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
624 if (!resource) {
625 encoder_stats_observer_->ClearAdaptationStats();
626 return;
627 }
628
629 std::map<VideoAdaptationReason, VideoAdaptationCounters> limitations;
630 for (auto& resource_counter : resource_limitations) {
631 std::map<VideoAdaptationReason, VideoAdaptationCounters>::iterator it;
632 bool inserted;
633 std::tie(it, inserted) = limitations.emplace(
634 GetReasonFromResource(resource_counter.first), resource_counter.second);
635 if (!inserted && it->second.Total() < resource_counter.second.Total()) {
636 it->second = resource_counter.second;
637 }
638 }
639
640 VideoAdaptationReason adaptation_reason = GetReasonFromResource(resource);
641 encoder_stats_observer_->OnAdaptationChanged(
642 adaptation_reason, limitations[VideoAdaptationReason::kCpu],
643 limitations[VideoAdaptationReason::kQuality]);
644
645 if (quality_rampup_experiment_) {
646 bool cpu_limited = limitations.at(VideoAdaptationReason::kCpu).Total() > 0;
647 auto qp_resolution_adaptations =
648 limitations.at(VideoAdaptationReason::kQuality).resolution_adaptations;
649 quality_rampup_experiment_->cpu_adapted(cpu_limited);
650 quality_rampup_experiment_->qp_resolution_adaptations(
651 qp_resolution_adaptations);
652 }
653
654 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ActiveCountsToString(limitations);
655}
656
657void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::MaybeUpdateTargetFrameRate() {
658 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
659 absl::optional<double> codec_max_frame_rate =
660 encoder_settings_.has_value()
661 ? absl::optional<double>(
662 encoder_settings_->video_codec().maxFramerate)
663 : absl::nullopt;
664 // The current target framerate is the maximum frame rate as specified by
665 // the current codec configuration or any limit imposed by the adaptation
666 // module. This is used to make sure overuse detection doesn't needlessly
667 // trigger in low and/or variable framerate scenarios.
668 absl::optional<double> target_frame_rate =
669 video_source_restrictions_.max_frame_rate();
670 if (!target_frame_rate.has_value() ||
671 (codec_max_frame_rate.has_value() &&
672 codec_max_frame_rate.value() < target_frame_rate.value())) {
673 target_frame_rate = codec_max_frame_rate;
674 }
675 encode_usage_resource_->SetTargetFrameRate(target_frame_rate);
676}
677
678void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::UpdateStatsAdaptationSettings() const {
679 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
680 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::AdaptationSettings cpu_settings(
681 IsResolutionScalingEnabled(degradation_preference_),
682 IsFramerateScalingEnabled(degradation_preference_));
683
684 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::AdaptationSettings quality_settings =
685 quality_scaler_resource_->is_started()
686 ? cpu_settings
687 : VideoStreamEncoderObserver::AdaptationSettings();
688 encoder_stats_observer_->UpdateAdaptationSettings(cpu_settings,
689 quality_settings);
690}
691
692// static
693std::string VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::ActiveCountsToString(
694 const std::map<VideoAdaptationReason, VideoAdaptationCounters>&
695 active_counts) {
696 rtc::StringBuilder ss;
697
698 ss << "Downgrade counts: fps: {";
699 for (auto& reason_count : active_counts) {
700 ss << ToString(reason_count.first) << ":";
701 ss << reason_count.second.fps_adaptations;
702 }
703 ss << "}, resolution {";
704 for (auto& reason_count : active_counts) {
705 ss << ToString(reason_count.first) << ":";
706 ss << reason_count.second.resolution_adaptations;
707 }
708 ss << "}";
709
710 return ss.Release();
711}
712
713void VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::OnQualityRampUp() {
714 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue_);
715 stream_adapter_->ClearRestrictions();
716 quality_rampup_experiment_.reset();
717}
718
719bool VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::IsSimulcast(
720 const VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config) {
721 const std::vector<VideoStream>& simulcast_layers =
722 encoder_config.simulcast_layers;
723 if (simulcast_layers.size() <= 1) {
724 return false;
725 }
726
727 if (simulcast_layers[0].active) {
728 // We can't distinguish between simulcast and singlecast when only the
729 // lowest spatial layer is active. Treat this case as simulcast.
730 return true;
731 }
732
733 int num_active_layers =
734 std::count_if(simulcast_layers.begin(), simulcast_layers.end(),
735 [](const VideoStream& layer) { return layer.active; });
736 return num_active_layers > 1;
737}
